                      "children": [
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "id": "qUQFs",
                          "name": "q5txt",
                          "fill": "#FAFAFA",
                          "content": "5. Could a smaller model explain 80% of the behavior?",
                          "fontFamily": "JetBrains Mono",
                          "fontSize": 13,
                          "fontWeight": "700"
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "frame",
                          "id": "2IIfB",
                          "name": "q5sp",
                          "width": "fill_container",
                          "height": 1
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "frame",
                          "id": "36TjZ",
                          "name": "q5badge",
                          "fill": "#22C55E15",
                          "cornerRadius": 10,
                          "padding": [
                            2,
                            6
                          ],
                          "children": [
                            {
                              "type": "text",
                              "id": "n0wV0",
                              "name": "q5bt",
                              "fill": "#22C55E",
                              "content": "ADDRESSED",
                              "fontFamily": "JetBrains Mono",
                              "fontSize": 9,
                              "fontWeight": "700",
                              "letterSpacing": 1
                            }
                          ]
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "oiyFg",
                      "name": "q5ans",
                      "fill": "#A1A1AA",
                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "content": "Yes — a simple chicken game between US and Iran with credibility externalities captures most dynamics. The multi-game framework adds precision but not structure.",
                      "fontFamily": "JetBrains Mono",
                      "fontSize": 12,
                      "fontWeight": "normal"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "XErQA",
                  "name": "counterargument",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "fill": "#141415",
                  "cornerRadius": 4,
                  "stroke": {
                    "thickness": 1,
                    "fill": "#F5A62340"
                  },
                  "layout": "vertical",
                  "gap": 12,
                  "padding": 20,
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "Gu0bg",
                      "name": "ctrTitle",
                      "fill": "#F5A623",
                      "content": "Steel-Manned Opposition",
                      "fontFamily": "Space Grotesk",
                      "fontSize": 14,
                      "fontWeight": "700"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "p9vWf",
                      "name": "ctrText",
                      "fill": "#A1A1AA",
                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "content": "The analysis overweights the historical trust destruction and underweights the power asymmetry. The US has demonstrated it can strike with impunity. Iran's 'grim trigger' may be rhetoric — they negotiated the JCPOA under severe sanctions pressure before. A credible 'take it or leave it' offer backed by continued military pressure could force settlement within 6 months.",
                      "fontFamily": "JetBrains Mono",
                      "fontSize": 12,
                      "fontWeight": "normal"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "luyOk",
                      "name": "ctrRebutLabel",
                      "fill": "#71717A",
                      "content": "Rebuttal:",
                      "fontFamily": "JetBrains Mono",
                      "fontSize": 11,
                      "fontWeight": "700"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "wKxPk",
                      "name": "ctrRebut",
                      "fill": "#71717A",
                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "content": "This argument fails because the 2015 context was fundamentally different — Iran had moderates in power who could sell the deal domestically. The adverse selection pattern has since eliminated moderates.",
                      "fontFamily": "JetBrains Mono",
                      "fontSize": 11,
                      "fontWeight": "normal"
                    }
                  ]
                },
